nl_problem:
# Task: spiral_matrix_ii
# Interface:
Class: Solution
Method: generateMatrix(self, arg1)

Given a positive integer n, generate an n x n matrix filled with elements from 1 to n^2 in spiral order.

Constraints:
- 1 <= n <= 20
lisp_spec:
(task
 (name "generateMatrix")
 (signature ( (n int) ) (list (list int)))
 (constraints
   (constraint "1 <= n <= 20")
 )
 (goal
   (description "Generate an n x n matrix filled with elements from 1 to n^2 in spiral order.")
   (rule "Start from the top-left corner and move right, then down, left, and up, repeating until all cells are filled.")
   (return "A 2D list representing the matrix in spiral order.")
 )
)
